1619924293472< /time>
< rating>
5</rating>
< Text>
OMG ... I'm a native New Yorker who has not had decent Pizza the entire time I've lived in the South Bay more than 6 plus years.... I keep driving past saying going I'll try it one day.  Well I had a friend visiting so tonight was the evening to try it. The pizza is absolutely amazing it is not inexpensive but could easily be shared between two people. Will do that next time... For now I have leftovers..... They do have gluten-free crust and the pizza is low carb which is nice as they make their own crust... In fact most of the ingredients on the pizza Bob the owner makes himself including the sausage and the turkey sausage. There are also vegan and vegetarian options. The cannoli is homemade and amazing. Looked at the rest of the menu and the sandwich and pasta selection looks great and is reasonably priced. They also offer a next door neighbor discount.  Highly recommend.... There's a reason they have been there 30 years and survives the covid pandemic. Looking forward to the restaurant opening for indoor dining. They have vintage arcade games..... At the moment they are mostly takeout but should be putting a tent up soon for outdoor dining.</Text>

< Text>
One of the most pleasant oil change experiences that I've had in a long time. I called in advance to request a quote and they immediately provided a fair price for the service. When I got there, the staff were friendly and took me in right away. It's a rather unique experience because you actually drive it into the shop and stay inside your vehicle during the entirety of the service. In the process, I was asked if there's a specific psi that I'd like the tires to be at or if they should go off of the recommended pressure. Another gentleman removed the air filter and showed it to me so I can decide whether or not to add an engine air filter change. When it's all said and done, I was in and out within 20 minutes. I was surprised at how efficiently the crew worked as a team! The yelp coupon was an added bonus, but they also provide a 10% discount to military personnel. Definitely coming back here for my other vehicle. Thanks for the fantastic, hassle-free experience!</Text>

< Review>
Not a fan of this place.  Used to go here years ago and one time while I was getting my oil changed, there was this guy outside (I'm assuming he was the owner) advertising this special deal you could buy to get 4 oil changes for the price of 3 (or was it 3 for the price of 2? It's been a while).  My family has a lot of cars so I bought it and took several of our cars there to get changes.

On my last oil change that the card provided me, I brought in my personal car, and the guy who had sold me the special deal recognized me and didn't seem happy to see me.  Whatever, I thought.  I also noticed that no one asked if my coolant or wiper fluids needed refilling or anything like that, which they usually did.  They seemed to want to hurry me out of there as fast as they could.

I got the oil change on my car and then drove back to Chico later that day where I was attending college at the time.  A little after I got back to Chico, I found out that they didn't screw the oil filter all the way in and oil had been leaking all the way back from Livermore.  This could have done irreparable damage to my car (though luckily it didn't) and I'm legitimately convinced that they were butt-hurt that I used my oil card to get the "free" change so that they didn't give me as good of service as they would have given someone else.  I had to get another oil change back in Chico because I was back in school for the semester and couldn't drive back to Livermore, and you can bet I never used Oil Changers' services again.< /Review>

I recently visited this Oil Changers location to get my wife's car serviced.  The experience at the shop was fine, it's what happened next that really has motivated me to write this review.

So I get home park the car and gave my wife the keys thinking nothing more of it.  Two days later I notice a massive oil spill on my driveway.  After some troubleshooting I find the problem, someone did not tighten my oil filter so the car literally leaked all the oil in it's engine on my driveway.

So I went and bought some oil to refill the engine and spent hours cleaning up my driveway (the oil is still not all out).

The leadership at the Oil Changers have been very responsive to my issue but I hope that my car doesn't have any real damage.  I will update this review (if I can) as things develop.

Words of wisdom, trust but verify that anyone working on your car knows what they are doing.<//Review>

First Bad Customer Service Experience I Have Ever Had With Verizon

Yesterday, I was so greatly helped by Sales Associate Alexyz from the Glendora store, not. I went to the store in order to upgrade my phone to the Galaxy Note 9. After being provided a few options, Alexyz made it clear to me that I couldn't leave the store with a new phone without having to pay $200+ and I couldn't apply it to my next bill. Needless to say I walked out the store with my old phone, exclaiming to the rest of the store that I would make it happen at the online Verizon store. Hi, this is Alexyz here from Verizon. Come visit us at the Glendora Marketplace store to chat about the great items saved in your cart. < review>
The view from the entrance includes a red statue, see below. The food overall was wonderful. The cheese plate was delicious though I personally don't like cheese enough to order at restaurants as a plate. The Myer lemon salad was extremely refreshing, simple lemon dressing with leaves slathered with cheese. Delicious! The pastas were wonderful as well, the textures of the pasta, cooked to perfection.  The pork ragu was good, the pesto ultimately was my favorite!  Had to have some cauliflower for more fiber and the tiramisu was delicious.< /review>

< Review>
I was so excited to eat at Oenotri as they are recommended in Michelin guide and claim to offer Neapolitan pizza from the traditional stone oven. I‚Äôve been to Naples, Italy and LOVE Neapolitan pizza. While the place was nice and full of people, the two pizzas that we ordered - classic margarita and zucchini - were not even close to the pizza I ate in Naples. The dough was NOT stretchy and chewy, but stiff. You can see the sharp edges after the bite. I wish they put more mozzarella, as I could hardly taste any, and basil leafs were also very sparse. All in all, maybe for someone that never tasted the authentic Neapolitan pizza before, it might be ok. Otherwise, don‚Äôt waste your time.<//Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating><userid>103870908741682036909< /userid><review>We had only one dinner in Napa on a short trip, so I was obsessing over where to go. We ultimately chose Oenotri because of its location close to our hotel, the unique and constantly-changing items on the menu, the more laid-back vibe, and of course, the food that gets consistently rave reviews. We chose well!

Our server was Devany, and we adored her immediately. We ordered a cocktail each, feeling a bit wined out from our first-ever tasting day in Napa, then decided on sharing the Intenso pizza and a pasta ragu with meat sauce and fusilli noodles. As a couple who generally avoids carbs, we were over the moon in love with our indulgent meal! The Intenso is a very non-traditional pizza that includes pistachios and red onions, no red sauce to be found. The pasta was literal perfection, reminded us of a rustic Old World-style pasta dish, and we about got into a fight over licking the bowl clean.

For dessert, we chose the panna cotta and it was delightful. We learned that Oenotri grows and uses many of its ingredients, including herbs, berries, and Meyer lemons, and you could taste the freshness in everything.

The service is team-style, which we really appreciated. We always had full glasses and never had any dirty plates or anything, plus everyone is extremely knowledgeable and friendly. The ambiance is romantic and cozy, but very laid-back. Prices are also super reasonable, a pleasant surprise in this area. Knowing how many incredible restaurant choices there are in Napa, we would happily come back here!<//review><Name>Taryn Shorr< /Name><Pictures>None<//Pictures></record>
</dataset><record>

Our reservation was at 6:15 pm. We were running a few minutes late so I called to let the restaurant know (at 6:21 pm). The gentleman who answered the call asked for my last name and told me no problem. When we showed up at around 6:30 pm, the female receptionist at the front told us it would be another 20 min. I told her that our reservation was at 6:15 pm. She said that since we were late for more than 30 min (or they only hold the table for 30 min), basically something along that line, they sit other guests first. First of all, our reservation was at 6:15 pm, so we were NOT 30 min late. Second of all, I did call to tell them that we were a few minutes late. I informed the female receptionist that I did call at around 6:20 pm and I could even show her the phone record. She then said that she doesn‚Äôt know who I spoke to but she did not receive such a message. OK, so if your team can‚Äôt communicate, it‚Äôs NOT my fault!!!
There was another party waiting whose reservation was also 6:15 pm. Here is what I think actually happened. Our table was NEVER ready at 6:15 pm. And you know what? It‚Äôs OK, it happens. Sometimes the party before us decided to have another drink or maybe they were involved in an interesting conversation and decided to sit there for longer than expected.
Instead of just telling us that, your female receptionist basically told me that it‚Äôs my fault that she had to give away our table. It‚Äôs my 2nd time at this restaurant and I won‚Äôt be back. Food is generally good, some dishes are better than others, but hey it‚Äôs Napa Valley, plenty of other better places to dine without having to deal with unpleasant receptionist.<//Review>

< Review>
Let me start by saying that the mushroom pasta dish was absolutely delicious. However, it was TINY!! I have never been to an Italian restaurant at any price point that didn't serve some sort of bread and olive oil or butter, but they did not. We were never offered wine... the waitress just took the wine glasses off of our table and the bus person served us water. We asked what the "pig face fries" are that are on the menu and received an absolutely disgusting explanation about how they "rip the meat off the skull of the pig and fry it up" to use all parts of the animal. I'm by no means a vegetarian, but it completely grossed me out, and the waitress acted annoyed that I was taken aback by her explanation and just walked away. Then... we waited for an HOUR between when we sat and quickly ordered and when our dishes came with absolutely no explanation or apology. Horrible experience. Horrible. There is clearly a very gifted chef there, though, because the tiny portions of food that we did finally receive after staring at our water for an hour were delightful. We left and literally walked directly to Gott's and ordered a second meal to share to compensate for the lack of food we'd just had. We were there on this past Sunday the 11th, 2018.<//Review>

1554318205530</Date>
< rating>
5< /rating>
<Review>Stellar.  Delicious.  Very well-crafted food from fresh ingredients, and the first place in North America that my partner has loved the pasta alla carbonara!  My gigli pasta in a pork ragout was comfort food raised to an art form.  The pizza we shared for a starter was perfectly done.  Their menu selection of pizzas was a bit odd, only one appealed to us but that one turned out to be excellent.  Their menu changes daily so take my kvetching about that selection with a grain of salt, and I'm guessing they'll probably make you a custom pizza (within reason) if you ask, because it's a high-service sort of place.

Don't just look at the dessert menu if you like a drink after dinner... they have a nice assortment of excellent grappa and I'm sure many other things besides the selections mentioned on the dessert card.

It's a bit of a noisy place, with hard surfaces and a bunch of people chatting (likely about how much they were enjoying dinner) so keep that in mind if you need a quiet dinner experience, but if you want excellent food in the Italian tradition of fresh, high-quality ingredients and careful prep.  We'll be back.</Review><Pics>None< /Pics>< Resp>
None</Resp>

< Text>
We came here on a Saturday night as a group of 11 girls (made a reservation prior to coming). I only had the pizza appetizer, which was mediocre at best. The service here was terribly slow. We had to request our waiter to bring bread for the table at least 3 times before we actually got any. Understandably, most places do not give individual checks for large groups; however, they‚Äôll usually let you split the check evenly among each person (i.e. 11 credit cards in this case). This place however didn‚Äôt allow that. The max amount of credit cards they would allow is ‚Äú4 or 5‚Äù? In terms of food, most of my friends ordered the pasta and they all said that it was very tasty.< /Text>

< Text>
I had supper here while on my honeymoon.  I was tickled to find 2 of my favorite drinks (Sazerac and Vieux Carre) but my wife couldn't get her favorite drink, a vodka martini with blue cheese stuffed olives.  When I told our server, Mike, this he asked what kind of vodka she liked and he didn't say anything, but we saw him at the bar stuffing olives with blue cheese and making the drink for her.  That is the kind of service needs to be recognized.  The pizza and canoli was first rate too, but thanks to Mike for going to the trouble to make a memorable moment for us.<//Text>

<Rate>4<//Rate><review>Came in on a Friday night for dinner around 21:00hrs and got a table for two right away. Picked out a bottle of Chenin Blanc and our waiter Damian was able to help us choose some complimenting dishes. We had the yellowfin crudo, Torchio with short rib, and Tagliatelle with shrimp.  Tuna was nice and simple and fresh, pasta for both dishes were nice and firm and had good flavor. One beefy, but not overly powering, and the shrimp had a good seafood taste, but may be too fishy for some, like my dining companion.

We had the chocolate cannoncini for dessert, described as a  croissant with chocolate cream. Was a bit harder than I expected, but soft tasting finish to the meal.  Would have preferred a darker chocolate taste.

Would return again if I was in the area.

Damian was knowledgeable about their food and made great recommendations to cater to our tarred and was pleasant throughout the whole dinner.< /review>< Pictures>

< GmapID>
0x8085065d44d04ad3:0x5c8a199dd2540770</GmapID>
<Time>1401817900046< /Time>< Review>
I was in Napa on vacation and asked Adam at the Vitners collective where he'd recommend for the best neapolitan Pizza in the area, without hesitation he effused about Oenotri.  So we tried it for dinner , and it wasn't as advertised it was transcendent!  I obsess over neapolitan Pizza, everywhere I go and including New York and my hometown of Cleveland, this is the new number one for me.  It was so good, my wife and I returned the next day for lunch and waited a half hour to be among the first to eat.  Also, tried the trompotti pasta, which was akin to eating candy, light perfectly paired with a simple cream based sauce with fresh split peas,green garlic and pesto.  The freshness of all the produce we had is hard to fairly describe, it's almost a secret weapon here.  But the dough deserves it, they even lavish a pre coat of 1 month old or less olive oil , then a second coat after baking.  between the overnite rise and the attention to detail the result is a crust that is the perfect balance of lightness and pliable crispness.  Bravo!< /Review>

< userid>
101674903013927661687< /userid>
< name>
Nate Tagulao<//name>
<date>1605061522156< /date><rate>3<//rate>< review>
I was craving for some taco truck food and found this place thru Yelp. It was easy enough to find and the customer service was pretty quick and the guys working were friendly.

I was very hungry and decided to try a bunch of their menu items. I ordered a Mexican style hot dog, steak fries, and four tacos each with a different meat. The hot dog was meh. It had some kick from the peppers on top but I really didn't taste much of the sausage or the bacon that it was wrapped in. The steak fries were just ok too. The fries weren't really crispy and the steak felt dry. The green chili sauce added a lot of flavor and really made up for everything else. It was definitely filling. All four tacos were pretty standard, I didnt feel like they wowed me. The steak one was, again, dry. The birria had nice flavor but it felt muted compared to other birria I've had. The pastor wasn't very flavorful to me. The cabeza was easily my favorite part of the meal. It was flavorful, tender and made for a satisfying two-bite taco.

Overall, I would say I didn't go completely crazy about this place and its food. It wasn't really bad by any means but it definitely didn't fulfill my taco truck cravings. Maybe I came on an off night, I would probably try it again later should it cross my mind.</review>

Awesome food truck! They have really delicious tacos. I really liked the way they fried their tortillas a little longer so it was a little crispy. They had decent tasting meats. <Rate>5<//Rate>< text>
You always hear about the dread of going to the post office, and I admit every time I go into a post office I've never been in I'm anxious to see how it'll go. This post office is great.

While some of the employees are slower than others servicing customers, most are quick and all of the employees are really nice.

They do often have line for picking up mail (which is always separate from the line for customers requiring other service), as there always seems to be issues with local community mailboxes  being broken into, however they have at least one employee who's designated job is to help these customers.

There are 3-4 self-service machines if you're short on time and the line to be helped is long as well.

Great post office for a city of this size.<//text>

<Text>Chicken Ranch is a funny name for a small, out of the way casino. The road leading to the casino is pretty tore up & a bit misleading. Just as you think something is wrong or maybe it's the wrong road, there it is! The casino is under construction as they are building a brand new bingo hall. They have moved the parking lot to across the street which, as of now is gravel. After finding your way in (main entrance is gated off) Chicken Ranch offers a variety of slots but no tables. It is a bit smokey & offers no non-smoking areas, except the bingo hall. There is a restaurant inside that offers very good food. It's a small cafe style, to sit g eat or they have finger foods available as well. They seem to be short staffed on waitresses often so don't count on one coming to offer a drink. Also only one ticket machine in the whole place or you can change a ticket at the cash cage where 2 ladies sit. If the place is packed which it usually is, plan on waiting in a line. Other than not having enough slots to accommodate all the players who visit it's great. Benches are available to those who just like to sit, free wifi, self serve coffee bar & free parking lot shuttle service are a few amenities offered here.<//Text><user_id>101513405682403069692< /user_id><gmapID>0x8090c376a33d6a81:0x7e0da7d4e1a54c66<//gmapID>< Response>

<Name>Greg Smith< /Name><Date>1495948113638</Date>< Rating>
3<//Rating>
<user>106198963285821922142</user>< review>
Bingo staff are by far the friendliest in the area and help make playing bingo more enjoyable. They are polite and are constantly ready to help anyone in need. They get to know the "regulars" and make everyone feel special and welcome to tl play.
The casino, however, is small and not a comfortable environment to gamble in.  Between tight/cramped  spaces, constantly full of smoke and its clientele I usually don't like to spend much time in playing there.  The machines appear to be set amongst the lowest "payout" in comparison to similar casinos. The players card is even lacking any real incentive to return with very little "free play". They lack updated games that are popular.  The casino also has an extremely short supply of the more desired machines that lead to customers waiting for available machines and players often saving them as they leave for extended periods of time, often times not returning. The casino also allows non-playing customers tie up popular machines by to sitting and visiting with others as waiting customers look on and wait. Because of it's location the casino has an issue with subjects obviously under the influence of narcotics and often ask for money from other customers. Unlike the bingo hall, where they continuously  make changes for the better, the casino fails to do so.< /review>

Had a wonderful time playing Bingo.  But had a lossy dinner.  It took one hour and ten minutes to get three Meat Loaf dinners and one Ribeye.   The excuse was that they got busy had to get everyone's food out and ours would be ready soon.  We were the third table in and people who came after us were served, eat and left before we got our food.  We asked our waitress about our food and she kept saying it will be a while.  My husband and daughter are both diabetic and had already given their insulin.  Finally we asked to see a manager and she acted like we just wanted a discount and we just wanted food.  She said it is ready do we want it or should she cancel it. We said we wanted it. She said she would give us a discount anyway.  We said thank you but we need our food.  Ten minutes later we got our food.  Then we had to wait on our check.  Instead of two checks with a discount we we got one check and no discount.  We tried to pay our bill and the girl never came back finally we asked to see the manager again and started out and went back and talked to the waitress for ten more minutes and we finally got our bill paied. We were very upset about the attitude of the waitress and the manager.  I was manager of Mesquite Star Food and Beverage and would never have treated a customer like that without even a smile.  Not good business.</Review>
